SIMPLE: insufflation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insufflation
<hw>In`suf*fla"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insuffatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>insuffation</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
in, and <er>Sufflation</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of breathing on or into
anything</def>; especially: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The
breathing upon a person in the sacrament of baptism to symbolize the
inspiration of a new spiritual life.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The act of blowing (a gas, powder, or vapor) into
any cavity of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insuitable</ent>⟦br⟧
